                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1595874158518-funding-agency-updates" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1595874158518-funding-agency-updates" aria-controls="accordion-content-1595874158518-funding-agency-updates" aria-expanded="false">
                            Funding Agency Updates
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1595874158518-funding-agency-updates" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1595874158518-funding-agency-updates">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1595874158518 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f259ad76-34cc-46fe-ab43-10fddd8b7bb0" >

    <p>The Canadian Institutes of Health Research (CIHR) have released a statement on May 1, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/51952.html">Planning for the Fall Project Grant Competition – May 1, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a><br> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>The Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC) has released a statement on April 21, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Media-Media/NewsDetail-DetailNouvelles_eng.asp?ID=1139">NSERC program information in relation to COVID-19&nbsp;– April 21, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>The Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council (SSHRC) has released a statement on April 9, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/news_room-salle_de_presse/covid-19-eng.aspx">COVID-19: Impacts on SSHRC's policies and programs – April 9, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>The National Research Council of Canada (NRC) has released a statement on April 9, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://nrc.canada.ca/en/updated-statement-national-research-council-canada-continued-support-clients-collaborators-during" target="_blank">Continued support for clients and collaborators during COVID-19&nbsp;– June 15, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>Mitacs has released a statement on March 19, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.mitacs.ca/en/newsroom/news-release/update-covid-19-coronavirus-march-19-2020">Update on COVID-19 (coronavirus) – March 19, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>The three federal granting agencies (CHIR, NSERC, SSHRC) have released a statement on March 16, 2020.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/news_room-salle_de_presse/latest_news-nouvelles_recentes/2020/covid-19_tri-agency-trois-organismes-eng.aspx">Tri-agency message on&nbsp;COVID-19 – March 16, 2020<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>The Tri-Council has also released a statement regarding travel fees relating to travel disruptions caused by COVID-19 on March 6, 2020. The statement can be found on the Government of Canada website.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/news_room-salle_de_presse/latest_news-nouvelles_recentes/2020/covid-19-eng.aspx">Notice to researchers about the eligibility of travel fees for disruptions caused by&nbsp;COVID-19<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul> 
